text: The Division of Dunkley is an Australian Electoral Division in Victoria. It was set up in 1984 and is named for Louisa Margaret Dunkley, a trade unionist and campaigner for equal pay for women. It covers an area of 140 km2 in the southern suburbs of Melbourne. It includes Frankston, Mornington and Mount Eliza. ==Members== Member Party Term Bob Chynoweth Labor 1984–1990 Frank Ford Liberal 1990–1993 Bob Chynoweth Labor 1993–1996 Bruce Billson Liberal 1996–present In 2013 Bruce Billson became the Minister for Small Business in the Abbott Government. ==Election results== ==References== ==Other websites== * Division of Dunkley – Australian Electoral Commission * Bruce Billson's website Category:Electoral divisions of Victoria, Australia Category:1984 establishments in Australia
